            <string name="1" value="Which one of these is part of the basic alchemy where the total amount of the material does not change, and that 'no item can be created from nothing'?\n(Author:Carson)\r\n#b#L0#Circulation#l\n#L1#Exchange#l\n#L2#Convert#l\n#L3#Security#l" />
            <string name="2" value="What's the most important aspect of experiencing science?\n(Author:Hughes the Fuse)\r\n#b#L0#Rules#l\n#L1#Formula#l\n#L2#Understanding#l\n#L3#Experiment#l" />
            <string name="3" value="Which of these ductility theories are used when making Weight Earrings?\n(Author:Moren)\r\n#b#L0#Ductility Theory of Gravity#l\n#L1#Ductility Theory of Expansion#l\n#L2#Ductility Theory of Weight#l\n#L3#Ductility Theory of Minimalization#l" />
